cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI

This paper is about learning-to-rank (LTR) systems, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) applications. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes new counterfactual approaches to correct for biases in LTR systems, which involves statistical modeling and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of click data, which is a form of user behavior data, and the methods proposed can be applied to other domains beyond IR and NLP, such as cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social media analysis (cs.SI).
